# 🧠 Gesture-Based Assistive Communication Using TinyML & FSK

## Overview

Gesture-Based Assistive Communication Using TinyML & FSK is an embedded assistive technology system designed to help individuals with speech or motor impairments communicate using hand gestures.

The system captures motion data using an IMU sensor, processes it with lightweight machine learning models deployed using TinyML, and transmits the interpreted gesture using Frequency Shift Keying (FSK) communication. The decoded gesture is then converted into readable text or speech output.

This project demonstrates how **embedded AI, signal processing, and digital communication techniques** can be combined to create an affordable and real-time assistive communication solution that operates entirely on edge devices without cloud dependency.

---

# ❗ Problem Statement

Individuals affected by conditions such as **paralysis, ALS, stroke, or severe speech impairments** often face significant challenges in expressing their needs.

Many existing assistive communication devices are:

* Expensive
* Complex to operate
* Dependent on internet connectivity

This project aims to provide a **low-cost, portable, and real-time embedded communication system** that allows users to communicate through simple hand gestures.

---

# 🎯 Project Objectives

* Develop a gesture recognition system using motion sensors.
* Implement TinyML models for real-time classification on embedded hardware.
* Transmit gesture data using **Frequency Shift Keying (FSK)** communication.
* Analyze gesture signal patterns using **MATLAB**.
* Provide visualization and monitoring using a **Python-based interface**.

---

# ⚙️ System Architecture

## 1️⃣ Motion Sensing Module

An **MPU6050 accelerometer and gyroscope** captures motion and orientation data generated by hand gestures.

## 2️⃣ Embedded Processing

A microcontroller (such as **ESP32**) processes the sensor data and runs a **TinyML model** that classifies gestures in real time.

## 3️⃣ Signal Processing & Analysis

MATLAB is used to:

* Analyze sensor data
* Visualize waveform patterns
* Study gesture signal behavior
* Design and test signal processing algorithms

## 4️⃣ Communication Module

The classified gesture data is encoded and transmitted using **Frequency Shift Keying (FSK)**, a digital modulation technique known for reliable data transmission.

## 5️⃣ Receiver & User Interface

The receiver decodes the transmitted signal and displays the interpreted gesture as **text or speech** using a Python-based visualization interface.

